What's new: 
- Performance improvements
- Bug fixes
Explore airports now with our brand new feature. Display terminal maps or find facilities like WiFi, relax zones, shops, showers & much more.

- you can now enter billing details when booking your flight
- search now provides more details about flights (food, power, etc.)
- you can now specify both takeoff and landing times in filters
- UI improvements
- bugfixes

- Performance improvements
- Bug fixes
Easily share your destination with friends!

Ever wanted to share a flight with your friends? Starting today you can just tap an icon to easily share your search results, bookings and more. We've also improved the home page and made some cool features available to guests as well as signed in users.

Based on your feedback we've been working on our login options. Now you can use your booking number to sign in and access the app's features without creating an account. And there are even more login improvements to look forward to in the future. In this release, we've also included some minor improvements to the booking page.

Do you want your friends to join you on an epic trip? Or maybe someone you know is planning to travel soon. Invite them to the Kiwi.com app with our 'Refer a friend' feature and claim sweet bonuses for you and your friends. Based on your feedback we've also improved the login screen for a smoother user experience.
Today's update may appear on a bit smaller size, but the contents are pretty significant. Beginning today you can use Paypal to book your flights!

We are always striving to bring you the best flight deals there are. In today's update we are happy to announce, that we have integrated the metasearch Kayak into our search results, so now you have even more options available for your journey!
- Bug fixes

The time has come for a big update! In our mission to provide you with the widest possible choice in travel, we've expanded our offering to include selected trains. You can even combine flights & trains in one trip! And to make your journey even more enjoyable, we've organised a number of vouchers for you to use at various airports. These are already available from our "Export Airport" feature.
- Bugfixes

In today's update we're proud to unveil a completely redesigned page for My Bookings. You can find all the information you'll ever need for your trip there, as well as additional services like accommodation, car hire & much more. We've worked hard to make it as user-friendly as possible and we hope you enjoy it!

Apart from getting rid of bugs, we've been experimenting a bit. Some of you might notice a difference when booking accommodation for your trip. We hope you like it! If you don't see any changes, don't worry, everybody will get a turn!
Bugfixes

This week we found two bugs. One in the app and the other in a bar of chocolate! Of course, we went around the office offering our colleagues a bite of the chocolate before we threw it away. Then we fixed the app. Hope you enjoy this bug-free version.

Thanks for updating the Kiwi.com app. As always, we’re doing everything we can to improve your travel experience. 
Changes? There were a few. Bugs? Squashed some of those too. 
Let’s break it down for you:
• Explore Destination 2.0
Check out your destination before you arrive and get settled in to your hotel. Locate and dine at favorite local restaurants. Visit your destinations most popular tourist attractions, hangouts, museums, and landmarks and then share them with your friends.  
• Extermination index
We eliminated some nasty bugs triggering bothersome offline alerts and providing incorrect locations in our throw away ticket info. 
• Keep that feedback coming 
We really appreciate it. It helps us focus our design and development efforts to provide you with the very best mobile user experience.

Thanks for updating the Kiwi.com app. And, welcome to a completely redesigned search.
Say what?
I says, we’ve given the app a major user experience overhaul. So, in addition to all the visual enhancements, the search flow is vastly improved. It’s more streamlined and straightforward. Users arrive at results much faster. & those results are now easier to scan and work with. The place picker, too, was improved quite a bit. It’s more organized and generally clearer. You’ll even notice us working on a new bottom-oriented navigation which is in its early stage iterations.
We’re proud of what we were able to accomplish with this redesign for you, our users. Please, don’t hesitate to let us know what you think. Enjoy.
